Quaker Oats Co said it filed a shelfregistration with the Securities and Exchange Commissioncovering up to 250 mln dlrs in debt securities.    The company said it may offer the securites in one or moreissues, from time to time, over the next two years.    Proceeds will be used to repay short term debt issued inconnection with Quaker Oats' recent acquisitions and for othercorporate purposes, it said.    Underwriters may include Salomon Brothers Inc and Goldman,Sachs and Co. Reuter&#3;